obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_3727  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1: In a neuronal culture model of LTP, activation of NMDARs by bath application of the coagonist glycine causes an increase in the surface expression of endogenous GluA1-containing AMPARs compared to untreated control cells. ShRNA-mediated Stx-3 KD significantly impaired both glycine-induced increases in GluA1 surface expression in culture and LTP recorded in acute slices.\nFigure 2: mEPSC amplitude nor its frequency were affected by the Stx-3 KD. Thus, postsynaptic Stx-3 is not required for basal transmission.. Experimental description: M&M:CD1 (Charles River) mice (8-12 g) were prepared for stereotactic injection of lentiviruses using standard procedures." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9900-4233" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-19" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3727" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

